    "The size of the granulated slag particles typically ranges from 1 to over 100 µm, with most particles under 45 µm and a surface area of approximately 400-600 m 2 /kg.",
    "The chemical composition of GGBFS, which contains about 40% silicon dioxide and 40% calcium oxide (CaO), further emphasizes its effectiveness as a SCM for improving concrete properties [37,38].",
